  "raw_meta_yaml": "{% set name = \"xllim\" %}\n{% set version = \"2.0.10\" %}\n\npackage:\n  name: {{ name|lower }}\n  version: {{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/x/xllim/xllim-{{ version }}.tar.gz\n  sha256: c1e911e5569e150255e3823a15901bcfb3719c056ae11033c00d1e2a2849d405\n\nbuild:\n  number: 1\n  script:\n    - {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation\n  skip: true  # [py<311 or py>=313]  # >=3.11 requirement from NumPy 2, <3.13 from CARMA \n\nrequirements:\n  build:\n    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}\n    - {{ stdlib(\"c\") }}\n    - cmake >=3.21\n    - ninja\n    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]\n    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]\n    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]\n    - pybind11                               # [build_platform != target_platform]\n\n  host:\n    - python # Build python versions should not be constrained here\n    - pip\n    - setuptools >=42\n    - wheel\n    - scikit-build-core >=0.7.0,<1  \n    - numpy  # numpy build version is decided by the conda-forge-pinning-feedstock, cannot constrain it here. Good news, it's numpy 2\n    - boost  # Letting boost use the global pin to be compatible with other packages (and be rebuilt accordingly)\n    - armadillo >=12.6,<13  # 12.6 minimum tested; <13 bounds to compatible major ABI. Pulls libblas & liblapack.\n    - pybind11 >=2.12,<3  # replaces vendored extern/pybind11; <3 needed (API break)\n    - carma  # replaces vendored extern/carma\n    - libblas    # explicit host dep so run_exports propagate the correct BLAS runtime\n    - liblapack  # idem\n\n  run:\n    - python\n    - numpy\n    - h5py >=3.8,<4\n    # libblas/liblapack run_exports handle BLAS runtime automatically\n\ntest:\n  imports:\n    - xllim\n    - xllim._core\n    - xllim.cli\n    - xllim.utils\n  commands:\n    - xllim_cli --help  # [not win]\n    - python -m xllim.cli --help  # [win]  # console script wrapper unreliable on Windows (new process DLL activation)\n    - pip check\n  requires:\n    - pip\n\nabout:\n  home: https://github.com/xllim-tools/xllim\n  license: CECILL-C\n  license_file: LICENCE.txt\n  summary: 'Python package for XLLiM with C++ core'\n  description: |\n    xLLiM is a C++ with Python bindings implementation of Gaussian Locally-Linear Mapping. It can be used to perform efficient inversion of high-dimensional models.\n  doc_url: https://xllim-tools.github.io/xllim/\n  dev_url: https://github.com/xllim-tools/xllim\n\nextra:\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - ffrancois-inria\n    - stan-borkowski\n",
